18 B. A patient, guardian of a patient, or legally authorized
19 representative of a patient shall have the following
20 responsibilities:
21 1. To provide accurate and complete information concerning the
22 patient’s present complaints, past illnesses, hospitalizations,
23 medications, and other matters relating to his or her health;
